# Initialize & Set Up Seeknal Projects

Set up new seeknal projects and configure the development environment.

## When to Use

Use this skill when asked to create a new seeknal project, set up connections, or configure the workspace.

## Create a New Project

```bash
# Initialize in current directory
seeknal init --name my_project

# This creates:
# ├── seeknal_project.yml    # Project config
# ├── profiles.yml           # Connection credentials (gitignored)
# ├── .gitignore             # Pre-configured ignores
# ├── CLAUDE.md              # Agent conventions (auto-generated)
# ├── AGENTS.md              # Agent safety rules (auto-generated)
# ├── .claude/skills/        # Claude Code skills (auto-generated)
# └── seeknal/
#     ├── sources/
#     ├── transforms/
#     ├── feature_groups/
#     ├── models/
#     └── common/
```

## Configure Connections

Edit `profiles.yml` (never commit this file):

```yaml
# PostgreSQL
local_pg:
  type: postgresql
  host: localhost
  port: 5432
  database: mydb
  user: myuser
  password: mypass

# Iceberg (via Lakekeeper)
iceberg_catalog:
  type: iceberg
  catalog_url: http://localhost:8181
  warehouse: my-warehouse
```

## Project Configuration

Edit `seeknal_project.yml`:

```yaml
name: my_project
version: "1.0"
profile: default

# Source defaults (applied to all sources of matching type)
source_defaults:
  postgresql:
    connection: local_pg
```

## Add Data Files

Place CSV, Parquet, or JSONL files in a `data/` directory:

```bash
mkdir -p data
cp customers.csv data/
```

Then create a source pointing to it:

```bash
seeknal draft source customers
# Edit: set source: csv, table: "data/customers.csv"
seeknal dry-run draft_source_customers.yml
seeknal apply draft_source_customers.yml
```

## Verify Setup

```bash
seeknal plan                    # Should show empty DAG (no nodes yet)
seeknal repl                    # Interactive SQL shell (verifies DuckDB works)
```

## Regenerate Agent Docs

If CLAUDE.md or AGENTS.md are outdated:

```bash
seeknal docs regenerate         # Refresh from current project state
```

## Common Mistakes

- **Running commands outside project root**: `seeknal` commands must run from the directory containing `seeknal_project.yml`
- **Missing profiles.yml**: Connection-based sources will fail without credentials
- **Wrong profile key name**: Use canonical type names (`postgresql` not `postgres`) in `source_defaults:`
- **Committing secrets**: Ensure `profiles.yml` and `.env` are in `.gitignore`
